# Copy to `.env.release` (gitignored) and fill in a token before `bun run release:mac`
# or `bun run release:win`.
#
# The release scripts read GH_TOKEN from this file and export it for the `gh`
# CLI so uploads need no interactive `gh auth login`. Two token types work:
#   - Classic PAT with the `repo` scope
#   - Fine-grained PAT scoped to nomifun/nomifun-tauri with Contents: Read and write
#
# Keep it short-lived and revoke when no longer needed.
GH_TOKEN=ghp_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# Optional Windows Authenticode: thumbprint of a code-signing certificate already
# imported into the current-user certificate store. When set, `bun run release:win`
# (and `bun run build:win --signed`) will Authenticode-sign the NSIS installer.
# Omit or use `release:win -NoSigned` to ship updater-signed-only packages
# (SmartScreen / unknown-publisher warnings may appear on manual install).
# WINDOWS_CERTIFICATE_THUMBPRINT=A1B2C3D4E5F6...
